<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I&#39;m playing with fzf-el, but I don&#39;t like how fzf-find-file works since I&#39;m a dired junkie and like to use C-x C-f for both files and dirs.</p> <p>So, I tried this, hoping to use a universal arg when I want to fzf-find-file, and normal without.</p> <pre><code>(defun fzf-or-find-file () (interactive) (if (equal current-prefix-arg nil) (find-file) (fzf-find-file))) </code></pre> <p>This works with C-u M-x fzf-or-find-file (the fzf version runs), but when I DON&#39;T pass a Ctrl-u, find-file ... fails. I&#39;m sure I&#39;m calling it incorrectly here, but pointers welcome.</p> <p>The failure looks like <a href="https://i.imgur.com/A9eCKAq.png">this</a></p> <p>What&#39;d I do wrong?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/campbellm"> /u/campbellm </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wmkue3/elisp_help_calling_findfile/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wmkue3/elisp_help_calling_findfile/">[comments]</a></span>